('34252', '1', 'Place beans in large saucepan.'),
('34252', '2', 'Add enough water to cover beans.  Bring to boil. simmer on medium-low heat 2-1/2 hours or until tender.'),
('34252', '3', 'Cook bacon in large skillet on medium heat until crisp.'),
('34252', '4', 'Drain on paper towels, reserving drippings in skillet for later use.'),
('34252', '5', 'Crumble bacon.'),
('34252', '6', 'Add to beans along with the corn, sausage and onions. mix well.  Simmer on medium-low heat 1 hour.'),
('34252', '7', 'Stir flour into reserved bacon drippings in skillet. cook on medium-low heat until hot and bubbly, stirring frequently.  Gradually stir in water until well blended. cook on medium heat until mixture comes to boil and thickens, stirring constantly.'),
('34252', '8', 'Add to soup. simmer 30 min., stirring occasionally.  Stir in pepper.'),
('34253', '1', 'Cook bacon in a 10-inch heavy skillet over moderate heat, stirring frequently, until crisp, about 5 minutes.'),
('34253', '2', 'Transfer bacon with a slotted spoon to paper towels to drain, then add butter to fat in skillet and melt over moderate heat.'),
('34253', '3', 'Add corn, lima beans, bell pepper, and white and pale green parts of scallions and cook, stirring, 2 minutes.'),
('34253', '4', 'Add cream, water, salt, and pepper, then simmer, partially covered, until vegetables are tender, 10 to 15 minutes. Stir in bacon, scallion greens, and salt and pepper to taste.'),
('34254', '1', 'In a large bowl, cover lima beans with water, cover with a towel and soak overnight.'),
('34254', '2', 'In a large pot, add oxtails, onions, scallions, garlic, thyme, red pepper, paprika, bay leaf, hot sauce, and gravy master and marinate at least 4 hours or overnight in the refrigerator, stirring occasionally.'),
('34254', '3', 'Add enough water to just cover the oxtails and bring the mixture to a boil. Lower to a simmer, cover and cook 2 hours. Every 30 minutes for 2 hours add 2 cups of water or broth, alternating, as necessary, to keep oxtails covered with liquid.'),
('34254', '4', 'At 2 hours, add the beans, tomato paste, and 2 more cups of beef broth and water, if needed. Bring to a boil then simmer uncovered 2 hours, skimming fat off top and stirring occasionally. In the last 1/2 hour of cook time, season with 2 tablespoons salt.'),
('34254', '5', 'Serve with rice.'),
('34254', '6', 'Rinse rice 3 times to remove starch. Put rice in a medium saucepan. Fill saucepan with enough water to cover the rice by 1/2-inch or measure by placing your thumb tip on the rice and filling the pot with water until the water reaches the middle of your thumbnail. Bring rice to a simmer, cover and cook until tender and liquid is evaporated, about 15 minutes.'),
('34254', '7', 'Remove from heat and let rice stand another 5 minutes, covered.'),
('34257', '1', 'Bring all ingredients to a boil in a Dutch oven over medium-high heat, stirring often. Cover, reduce heat to low, and simmer, stirring occasionally, 25 minutes or until thoroughly heated.'),
('34258', '1', 'Sort and wash beans. place in a large Dutch oven. Cover with water to 2 inches above beans. cover and let stand 8 hours or overnight.'),
('34258', '2', 'Drain beans. Cover with water to 2 inches above beans, and bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat, and simmer 1 hour or until beans are tender.'),
('34258', '3', 'Drain beans.'),
('34258', '4', 'Preheat oven to 32'),
('34258', '5', 'While beans cook, heat oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium heat.'),
('34258', '6', 'Add onion, celery, carrot, and garlic. cook 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in oregano and tomatoes. simmer 10 minutes. Stir in parsley, dill, honey, salt, and pepper.'),
('34258', '7', 'Combine the cooked beans and tomato mixture in a 3-quart casserole coated with cooking spray.'),
('34258', '8', 'Bake at 325 for 1 hour.'),
('34259', '1', 'In a skillet, cook the bacon and onion over medium-high heat, stirring, until half-cooked and not yet crispy, about 8 minutes.  Set aside.'),
('34259', '2', 'In a large stockpot, add the water and tomatoes and bring to a boil over high heat.'),
('34259', '3', 'Add the live crabs and boil for 12 minutes.'),
('34259', '4', 'Remove the crabs and set aside to cool.  (If using carcasses, leave them in the pot.)  Reduce the heat to low and simmer for 1 hour.'),
('34259', '5', 'Meanwhile, remove the meat from the crabs and set aside.  As this is mysteriously complicated unless you are from Maryland, see the instructions below for guidance on how to shell a crab.'),
('34259', '6', 'After the soup has been simmering for 1 hour, add the celery, corn, green beans, peas, lima beans, potatoes, Old Bay seasoning, red chile flakes, and the reserved bacon and onion. if you have used crab carcasses and shells, strain the soup before adding the vegetables and discard the shells.  Simmer until the vegetables are cooked, about 30 minutes.  Season with salt.'),
('34259', '7', 'Add the reserved crab meat and add the fresh claw meat, stir, and serve.'),
('34259', '8', 'How to Pick Crabs'),
('34259', '9', 'Twist off the claws and legs.'),
('34259', '10', 'Place the crab on its back and pull the apron up and off.'),
('34259', '11', 'Cut the bottom shell just under the mouth with a knife.'),
('34259', '12', 'Remove and discard the spongy white gills, which are inedible.'),
('34259', '13', 'Snap the crab body into halves.'),
('34259', '14', 'Twist off the back fins.'),
('34259', '15', 'Crack the claws with a mallet to remove the claw meat.'),
('34259', '16', 'Remove the meat from the other parts with a nut pick.'),
('34260', '1', 'Heat oil in heavy large skillet over mediumheat.'),
('34260', '2', 'Add onion and sprinkle with coarsesalt. Saute until soft and translucent, about5 minutes.'),
('34260', '3', 'Add garlic. stir until fragrant,about 1 minute.'),
('34260', '4', 'Add tomatoes, corn, andlima beans. Reduce heat to medium-low,cover, and simmer until corn and limabeans are tender and tomatoes are soft,about 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.Season to taste with salt and pepper. DO AHEAD:Can be made 1 day ahead. Coverand chill. Rewarm before continuing.'),
('34260', '5', 'Stir in basil and serve.'),
('34261', '1', 'Bring 4 cups of water to a boil.'),
('34261', '2', 'Add dry lima beans, and boil for 2 to 3 minutes.'),
('34261', '3', 'Remove from heat, and allow the beans to sit, covered, for 1 to 2 hours to soften.'),
('34261', '4', 'Drain and rinse until water runs clear, discarding bean water.'),
('34261', '5', 'In a soup pot, saute vegetables in olive oil until onions and celery are translucent.'),
('34261', '6', 'Add lima beans, and saute for another 2 to 3 minutes.'),
('34261', '7', 'In the meantime, bring 4 cups of water to a boil.'),
('34261', '8', 'Add the vegetable bouillon to the boiling water, and stir until dissolved.'),
('34261', '9', 'Add broth to the sauteed vegetables and beans.'),
('34261', '10', 'Add remaining water, and allow soup to simmer over a low flame for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.'),
('34261', '11', 'Serve steaming hot.'),
('34262', '1', 'Cook meat in hot oil over medium-high heat in a large Dutch oven 6 to 8 minutes or until browned.'),
('34262', '2', 'Stir in frozen mixed vegetables, next 9 ingredients, and 1 1/2 qt. water, stirring to loosen particles from bottom of Dutch oven. Bring mixture to a boil over medium-high heat. cover, reduce heat to low, and simmer, stirring occasionally, 55 to 60 minutes or until potatoes are tender.'),
('34262', '3', 'Note: For testing purposes only, we used Knorr Chicken Bouillon cube.'),
('34263', '1', 'Watch how to make this recipe.'),
('34263', '2', 'Add the beans to a pot with enough cold water to cover well. Bring to a boil, lower the heat, cover, and simmer until just soft throughout but not quite cooked, approximately 50 to 80 minutes, depending on the beans.'),
('34263', '3', 'Drain and set aside.'),
('34263', '4', 'Preheat the oven to 325 degrees F.'),
('34263', '5', 'Heat olive oil over medium heat in a Dutch oven.'),
('34263', '6', 'Add onion and cook until soft.'),
('34263', '7', 'Add the garlic and cook for 30 seconds.'),
('34263', '8', 'Add tomatoes and their liquid, 2 cups water, honey, cloves, salt, and pepper and boil gently for 20 to 30 minutes or until it begins to thicken. Stir in the parsley and remove from heat.'),
('34263', '9', 'Place the beans in an oven-proof dish, pour tomato mixture on top, stir and spread mixture out evenly.'),
('34263', '10', 'Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours, or until beans are soft. (Check the dish during cooking and if needed, add a small amount of boiling water.) The dish will look crispy on top.'),
('34263', '11', 'Remove from the oven and let sit for 10 minutes before serving.'),
('34263', '12', 'Serve hot or at room temperature.'),
('34265', '1', 'Place lima beans in a Dutch oven or soup kettle. add water to cover by 2 in. Bring to a boil. boil for 2 minutes.'),
('34265', '2', 'Remove from the heat. cover and let stand for 1 hour.'),
('34265', '3', 'Drain and rinse beans, discard liquid.'),
('34265', '4', 'In a Dutch oven coated with nonstick cooking spray, cook onions and garlic until tender. Stir in the broth, ham, carrots, water, jalapeno, parsley, pepper and lima beans. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat. cover and simmer for 50 minutes or until beans are tender.'),
('34266', '1', 'Place whole tomatoes,  water, lima beans, corn, sliced carrots, chopped onion,  Old Bay seasoning, and beef broth,  in a  4 quart pot.'),
('34266', '2', 'Heat to simmer, cover, and cook for 5 minutes.'),
('34266', '3', 'Bring 1 gallon water to boil.'),
('34266', '4', 'Add crab claws and boil 6 minutes.'),
('34266', '5', 'Drain crab and set aside'),
('34266', '6', 'Stir crabmeat (and crabs claws, if desired) into tomato and vegetable mixture. Cover and simmer 10-15 minutes longer.'),
('34266', '7', 'Serve hot.'),
('34268', '1', 'Put cannellini beans in a medium pot, cover with water, and bring to a boil. Cover and turn off heat.'),
('34268', '2', 'Let sit 1 hour.'),
('34268', '3', 'Drain beans, then return to pot and add carrot, celery, halved onion, whole garlic cloves, parsley sprigs, thyme, and peppercorns. Cover with water by 1 in. and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to maintain a steady simmer and cook until beans are tender, 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Discard vegetables and herbs and let beans cool.'),
('34268', '4', 'Drain, reserving liquid, and set liquid and beans aside.'),
('34268', '5', 'Put 1 tbsp. olive oil, mushrooms, and 1 tsp. salt in a large (not nonstick) frying pan over high heat. Cook, stirring, until mushrooms stop giving off liquid and start to brown.'),
('34268', '6', 'Transfer to a large bowl.'),
('34268', '7', 'In same frying pan over medium-high heat, add remaining 2 tbsp. olive oil and chopped onion. Cook until onion is soft, 3 minutes.'),
('34268', '8', 'Add chopped garlic and cook, stirring, until fragrant, about 1 minute.'),
('34268', '9', 'Add vinegar and cook, scraping up any brown bits, until pan is almost dry. Return mushrooms to pan along with reserved beans and 1/4 cup reserved bean-cooking liquid. Cook, stirring, until well combined and hot. Stir in chopped parsley and salt and pepper to taste.'),
('34268', '10', 'Serve hot or warm.'),
('34271', '1', 'Watch how to make this recipe.'),
('34271', '2', 'Sprinkle the steak with salt and pepper. Set aside.'),
('34271', '3', 'In a large Dutch oven (preferably enameled cast iron) over medium-high heat, render the bacon until just starting to crisp, 6 to 7 minutes, stirring as needed.'),
('34271', '4', 'Remove 1 tablespoon of the bacon fat and set aside.'),
('34271', '5', 'Add the onions and jalapenos and cook until the onions are translucent, about 5 minutes more.'),
('34271', '6', 'Add in the garlic cook 1 to 2 minutes.'),
('34271', '7', 'Remove all from the pot to a small bowl. Set aside.'),
('34271', '8', 'Wipe down the inside of the pot, add the reserved 1 tablespoon bacon fat and, when starting to smoke, add in 1/3 to 1/2 of the steak and cook, stirring as needed until just starting to brown, about 8 minutes.'),
('34271', '9', 'Remove to the vegetable bowl, repeat with the remaining steak.'),
('34271', '10', 'Once the steak is cooked, deglaze with 1 tablespoon apple cider vinegar. Then return all the vegetables and cooked steak back to the pot and add in the beans, including the liquid in the can.'),
('34271', '11', 'Add the molasses, brown sugar, soy and ketchup, and stir to combine. Bring to a simmer over low heat, cover and cook for 2 hours, stirring every 20 to 30 minutes to assure that the bottom doesn''t stick.'),
('34271', '12', 'Add in more apple cider vinegar, a few tablespoons at a time to personal taste, and serve with crusty bread.'),
('34273', '1', 'Bring 4 cups water and 1 teaspoon salt to a boil in a medium, heavy saucepan. gradually whisk in grits. Reduce heat. simmer, uncovered, 20 to 25 minutes or until thick, stirring often.'),
('34273', '2', 'Remove from heat, and add 1/4 cup butter and Parmesan cheese, stirring until cheese melts. cover and keep warm.'),
('34273', '3', 'Heat 1 tablespoon oil in a saut&eacute. pan or large skillet over medium-high heat. add lima beans, onion, celery, and carrot. saut&eacute. 2 minutes.'),
('34273', '4', 'Add 1/2 cup water. cover, reduce heat, and simmer 15 minutes.'),
('34273', '5', 'Add corn. cook, uncovered, 3 to 5 minutes.'),
('34273', '6', 'Remove vegetables from pan. keep warm.'),
('34273', '7', 'Add remaining 1 tablespoon oil to pan, and heat. add shrimp, and cook 1 to 2 minutes on each side.'),
('34273', '8', 'Add ham and shallot. cook 2 minutes.'),
('34273', '9', 'Add white wine, and cook to deglaze pan (stirring to loosen particles from bottom of skillet).'),
('34273', '10', 'Add lima bean mixture and tomato halves to pan. Cook 1 to 2 minutes or until heated through. Stir in remaining 1/4 cup butter, lemon juice, and Tabasco sauce. season to taste with salt (about 1/4 teaspoon) and white pepper.'),
('34273', '11', 'Serve shrimp and succotash over hot grits.'),
('34274', '1', 'Sift together flour, salt, and sugar into a chilled large metal bowl. Set a grater over flour mixture and coarsely grate frozen butter into flour, gently lifting flour and tossing to coat butter.'),
('34274', '2', 'Drizzle ice water evenly over flour mixture and gently stir with a fork until incorporated. Turn out mixture onto a lightly floured surface and divide into 6 portions. With heel of your hand, smear each portion once or twice in a forward motion to help distribute fat. Gather dough together with scraper and form into a 6- to 7-inch square. Wrap in plastic wrap and chill at least 1 hour. (Dough will be lumpy and streaky.)'),
('34275', '1', 'In a large covered kettle, bring 6 quarts salted water to a rolling boil over high heat.'),
('34275', '2', 'Add the lobsters, cover, and cook for 10 minutes.'),
('34275', '3', 'Drain and cool under cold running water. With poultry shears, cut away the claw and tail shells and carefully remove the meat. If the lobsters are female, reserve the grainy red coral and chop finely. Cover and refrigerate the lobster meat and coral.'),
('34275', '4', 'With a sharp knife, cut the kernels off the cob, slicing from the top of the ear downward, but not too close to the cob. You should have about 4 cups. Using a small spoon, scrape the milky liquid from the cobs into a medium bowl.'),
('34275', '5', 'Add the kernels and reserve.'),
('34275', '6', 'In a medium saucepan of lightly salted boiling water, blanch the lima beans until almost tender, 3 to 5 minutes. Cool under cold running water.'),
('34275', '7', 'Drain and reserve.'),
('34275', '8', 'In a large heavy nonreactive saucepan, melt the butter over medium heat.'),
('34275', '9', 'Add the cream. When it begins to steam, add the corn and its pulp and cook for 10 minutes, stirring often until the liquid thickens slightly.'),
